<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Posts on JF</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/</link><description>Recent content in Posts on JF</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-US</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 16:23:59 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://jokobus.github.io/posts/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Deploy Hugo on your Homserver via GitHub Actions</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/hugo_github_workflow/</link><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 16:23:59 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/hugo_github_workflow/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="prerequisites"&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A GitHub account&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Hugo website in a private repository, pushed to GitHub&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Linux homeserver with Caddy Reverse Proxy running.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A domain (or duckdns)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If not, then this guide is not the perfect match for you (yet). However, you can get a GitHub account and set it up with this guide &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="https://jokobus.github.io/posts/git/"&gt;Git &amp;amp; GitHub Essentials&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/em&gt;. Another of my blogs covers &lt;a href="https://jokobus.github.io/posts/create_hugo_blog/"&gt;How to create a blog with Hugo&lt;/a&gt;
. Getting your own Linux homeserver is also doable, e.g. with a Raspi. Come back to this afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Install Custom Applications on Linux</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/linux/install-custom-applications-on-linux/</link><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 09:21:51 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/linux/install-custom-applications-on-linux/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview"&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When using Linux machines where you lack root privileges (sudo), you can still install applications locally. This guide covers how to set up standalone binaries (like VS Code, Obsidian, or custom tools) and integrate them into your desktop environment&amp;rsquo;s app launcher using &lt;code&gt;.desktop&lt;/code&gt; files.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="step-by-step-installation"&gt;Step-by-Step Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-download-and-prepare"&gt;1. Download and Prepare&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Download the executable or compressed archive (&lt;code&gt;.tar.gz&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;.zip&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;.AppImage&lt;/code&gt;) for your application. If it&amp;rsquo;s a folder, move it to a dedicated local bin directory.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Git &amp; GitHub</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/git/</link><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/git/</guid><description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Git is a distributed version control software system that is capable of managing versions of source code or data. It is often used to control source code by programmers who are developing software collaboratively.&amp;rdquo; [&lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Wikipedia as of 2025-05-30&lt;/a&gt;
]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="i-setup--configuration"&gt;I. Setup &amp;amp; Configuration&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-install-git"&gt;1. Install Git&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Test if installed: &lt;code&gt;git --version&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Windows&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;winget&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;-id&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Git&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="py"&gt;Git&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;-e&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;-source&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;winget&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;macOS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;brew install git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Linux&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Debian, Ubuntu, Raspberry Pi OS&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo apt install git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Arch Linux&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo pacman -S git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Fedora&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo dnf install git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# NixOS / Nix&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;nix-env -iA nixpkgs.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-install-github-cli-gh"&gt;2. Install GitHub CLI (&lt;code&gt;gh&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential for PRs and repo management from the terminal.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Avoid Python Package Import-Errors in VSCodium or VSCode</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/howto/vscodium_ignore-import-errors/</link><pubDate>Sun, 31 May 2026 16:17:11 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/howto/vscodium_ignore-import-errors/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If you are working with Conda environments, you might notice that VSCodium or VS Code shows &amp;ldquo;import not found&amp;rdquo; errors (red squiggly lines) even though your code runs perfectly fine in the terminal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This happens because the IDE&amp;rsquo;s Python extension doesn&amp;rsquo;t automatically know which Conda environment to use for its background linting and IntelliSense. By explicitly setting the interpreter path, you tell the IDE exactly where to look for your installed packages.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Tune VSCodium for Python</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/howto/vscodium_tune4python/</link><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 12:41:04 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/howto/vscodium_tune4python/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://vscodium.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;VSCodium&lt;/a&gt;
 is the Open-Source binaries version of the popular Visual Studio Code IDE, mainly developed by Microsoft.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, VSCodium lacks some nice features such as code auto complete, nice code coloring, funtcion preview at howver, etc. The good news is: You can easily enhance your VSCodium Experience, by following the following steps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="1-install-extensions"&gt;1. Install Extensions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Install the&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Python&lt;/strong&gt; and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pyright&lt;/strong&gt; (by ms-pyright)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extensions via the Extensions Store at the left, vertical bar in VSCodium.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Use Neoylayout</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/neoylayout/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Jun 2025 14:51:26 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/neoylayout/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is a short summary of the essentials of the keybord layout &lt;a href="https://neo-layout.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;neo-layout&lt;/a&gt;
 variant &lt;a href="https://neo-layout.org/Layouts/bone/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;em&gt;bone&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 for faster and healtier text (and math) typing on your PC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="windows"&gt;Windows&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To use it on Windows follow these steps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="install"&gt;Install&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Copy the &lt;em&gt;kbdbone.dll&lt;/em&gt; file in System32 to &lt;em&gt;C:\Windows\System32&lt;/em&gt; and the one in SysWOW64 to &lt;em&gt;C:\Windows\SysWOW64&lt;/em&gt; respectively. Grant access rights. (On 64-bit Windows you have to copy it with a 64-bit Programm, best by the Windows Explorer)&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>OOBE</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/windows/oobe/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Jun 2025 12:34:02 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/windows/oobe/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-is-oobe"&gt;What is OOBE?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OOBE is the Windows Out of Box Experience, that you have to click through after a fresh installation of Windows on your Computer. There you can set the system language, keyboard layout, connect to the internet and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="problem-1-windows-wants-to-force-you-to-use-a-microsoft-account"&gt;Problem 1: Windows wants to force you to use a Microsoft Account&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Microsoft wants you to use a Microsoft Account that is connected to their Cloud - to use all the amazing online Microsoft Features (and conveniently collect your data. Mpf). But instead of adding a Button &amp;ldquo;Use local account instead&amp;rdquo; they lay stones in your path. What a surprise! Solution 1 helps&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>SQL</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/programming/sql/</link><pubDate>Tue, 20 May 2025 16:22:04 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/programming/sql/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This post is my personal SQL Cheat Sheet, based on the SQL tutorial by &lt;a href="https://www.w3schools.com/sql/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;W3Schools&lt;/a&gt;
.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;tl;dr SQL let&amp;rsquo;s you access and manipulate databases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-sql"&gt;Why SQL&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SQL can execute queries, retrieve data, insert records, update records, delete record to/from a database as well as create/delete a database, create/delete tables in a database, create views and stored procedures in a database and finally set permissions on tables, procedures and views.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many database programs build on SQL, but add some (proprietary) functionalities.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Conda</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/conda/</link><pubDate>Tue, 13 May 2025 22:50:33 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/conda/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="why-conda"&gt;Why Conda?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Conda is an environment and package management system, widely used in scientific computing and data science. Very handy if you program in Python. Conda features:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Platform Compatibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Package Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Environment Management (you can switch easily)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Version control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dependency Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The handy thing about conda is that you can create a new environment for each project that you have. Then you install all the packages for each project in it&amp;rsquo;s own dedicated environment. Then you can swap back and forth to another project that might need totally different packages and versions. The different packages and versions are kind of &amp;lsquo;containerized&amp;rsquo; and don&amp;rsquo;t interfer with each other.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Custom Anki Card</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/howto/custom-anki-card/</link><pubDate>Fri, 02 May 2025 11:43:40 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/howto/custom-anki-card/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Today, I came accross my old Notes from my German Class at School. I decided to learn the stylistic devices (dt. &amp;ldquo;Stilmittel&amp;rdquo;) again. To do so, I want to use Anki and create a custom card with the three fields &lt;strong&gt;Name&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Definition&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;. In this guide, I will explain how to create a custom Anki card (template) with multiple fields and cross-learning. When the cards are created, I have to learn each three times.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Java</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/programming/java/</link><pubDate>Sun, 27 Apr 2025 15:53:33 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/programming/java/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is my personal Java Summary. There&amp;rsquo;s nothing special about it, I just published it, because I already have it in markdown format, so why not?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A huge Thank You to &lt;a href="https://www.w3schools.com/java/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;https://www.w3schools.com/java/java_scope.asp&lt;/a&gt;
. Most examples are more or less directly from the public Java Tutorial. Some of the more interesting I copied into my summary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="1-basics"&gt;1. Basics&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="compile--run"&gt;Compile &amp;amp; Run&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;C:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Users&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Yourname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Path&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;javac&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Main&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="py"&gt;java&lt;/span&gt;	&lt;span class="p"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Compile&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;C:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Users&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Yourname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Path&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;java&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Main&lt;/span&gt;		&lt;span class="p"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Execute&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="io"&gt;IO&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;number&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;out&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;println&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#34;bla&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;number&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="type-casting"&gt;Type casting&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;z&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// Widening cast: z = 5.0, done automatically&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;z&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// Narrowing cast: x = 5, need to specify the cast manually&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="strings"&gt;Strings&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;firstname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#34;Peter &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;lastname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#34;Pan&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;firstname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;toUpperCase&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;();&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;//PETER&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;firstname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;toLowerCase&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;();&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;//peter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;firstname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;length&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;();&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;firstname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;lastname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// Peter Pan, or&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;firstname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;concat&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;lastname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// Peter Pan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="string---integer-conversion"&gt;String &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; Integer Conversion&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;mystring&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;valueOf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;myint&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// if int myint = 5; -&amp;gt; mystring = &amp;#34;5&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;myint&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;valueOf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;mystring&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// if mystring = &amp;#34;10&amp;#34;; -&amp;gt; myint = 10; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="math-helpers"&gt;Math helpers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;max&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;myint&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;max&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;//10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;min&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;myint&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;abs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;myint&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;sqrt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;myint&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;randomNum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;random&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;101&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;// 0 to 100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="2-conditions--loops"&gt;2. Conditions &amp;amp; Loops&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="if-else-elseif"&gt;If, else, elseif&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;if, else, else if as in C&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How to include Scalable Vector Graphics (svg) in $\LaTeX$</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/latex/includesvg/</link><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2024 13:09:54 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/latex/includesvg/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;You may know the popular LaTeX package &lt;em&gt;graphicx&lt;/em&gt; which you can use as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-TeX" data-lang="TeX"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;\includegraphics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;[options]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;filename&lt;span class="nb"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;graphicx&lt;/em&gt; does not support svg, but there is the package called &lt;em&gt;svg&lt;/em&gt; that does the job.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-use-the-svg-package"&gt;How to use the &lt;em&gt;svg&lt;/em&gt; package:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Install &lt;a href="https://inkscape.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Inkscape&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On Windows you can use winget.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-PowerShell" data-lang="PowerShell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;winget&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;install&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;-e&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;-id&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Inkscape&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="py"&gt;Inkscape&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Copy your &lt;em&gt;image.svg&lt;/em&gt; file into your document root folder (= right next to your .tex file)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a MWE for your .tex file:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-TeX" data-lang="TeX"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;\documentclass&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;article&lt;span class="nb"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;\includepackage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;svg&lt;span class="nb"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;\begin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;document&lt;span class="nb"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;\begin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;figure&lt;span class="nb"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;\includesvg&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="na"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;image&lt;span class="nb"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;\end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;figure&lt;span class="nb"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;\end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;document&lt;span class="nb"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Notes:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How to create a blog with Hugo (full guide)</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/create_hugo_blog/</link><pubDate>Thu, 27 Jun 2024 10:43:10 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/create_hugo_blog/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is a short guide how to create a &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt;
 blog, using the &lt;a href="https://github.com/tomowang/hugo-theme-tailwind" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;tailwind&lt;/a&gt;
 theme, which is the one I&amp;rsquo;m currently using myself. This guide was written with unexperienced users in mind. If you follow this guide 1:1 you &lt;em&gt;should&lt;/em&gt; get a running instance (no guarantee of course). If you are confident with the topic, you can use this guide to get inspired and modify the steps to your own preference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although the following steps are for Windows, the whole process is the same for Linux/MacOS. Only some of the console commands are slightly different. E.g. instead of the powershell command &lt;em&gt;Start-process&lt;/em&gt; you can use &lt;em&gt;nano&lt;/em&gt; or &lt;em&gt;vim&lt;/em&gt; and instead of &lt;em&gt;winget&lt;/em&gt; you may use your distribution&amp;rsquo;s package manager or homebrew.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Linear Regression</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/linear_regression/</link><pubDate>Sun, 23 Jun 2024 11:50:21 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/linear_regression/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview"&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why and when do we need linear regression? In a nutshell, linear regression is used to predict data that has a &lt;strong&gt;linear&lt;/strong&gt; relationship. That means all the datapoints are roughly on a straight line (in 2D), resp. on a hyperplane (in 3D). Firstly, we find some expression for the linear relationship (e.g. in 2D: $y=a\cdot x + b$; where $a$ is the slope and $b$ is the y-intercept). Secondly, we use this expression to insert some data where we only know the $x$ value, but want to predict their unknown $y$ value.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Feedforward Phase</title><link>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/feedforward/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 May 2024 19:27:30 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://jokobus.github.io/posts/feedforward/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This article gives a quick overview over the feedforward phase of a Neural Network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="nodes"&gt;Nodes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Neural Network is made of many &lt;strong&gt;Nodes&lt;/strong&gt; that are connected to each other. Each Node itself is a very basic unit that does only do three things.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multiply each input with a weight and sum all inputs up. $y_{in} = \sum_{i=0}^m w_i\cdot x_i$, where $m$ is the number of inputs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process the single, scalar input value by some activation function $y_{out}=f(y_{in})$ where $y_{in}$ is the result from step 1 and $y_{out}$ is the result from step 1 after being applied to the activation function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Output the result $y_{out}$ to the next node&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, a single node pretty much looks like this:
&lt;div class="not-prose"&gt;
&lt;picture&gt;
 &lt;source type="image/webp" srcset="https://jokobus.github.io/posts/feedforward/images/Single_Node_hu_c0b419fe7808747b.webp 320w, https://jokobus.github.io/posts/feedforward/images/Single_Node_hu_bd9bea0247148daf.webp 640w" sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 100vw, 50vw" /&gt;
 &lt;source type="image/jpeg" srcset="https://jokobus.github.io/posts/feedforward/images/Single_Node_hu_4acf994b3a82f269.jpg 320w, https://jokobus.github.io/posts/feedforward/images/Single_Node_hu_c2b4bc9b37f65e46.jpg 640w" sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 100vw, 50vw" /&gt;
 &lt;img class="h-auto max-w-full rounded-lg" src="https://jokobus.github.io/posts/feedforward/images/Single_Node_hu_c2b4bc9b37f65e46.jpg" width="776" height="436" alt="Figure 1: A single Node with its weights" title="Figure 1: A single Node with its weights" loading="lazy" /&gt;
 &lt;/picture&gt;&lt;p class="text-sm text-center text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-300"&gt;Figure 1: A single Node with its weights&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>